full_text:
Any attempts to undermine the postal service, particularly if for political purposes, strikes at the heart of our communities, and puts people at physical risk.

It’s unacceptable, and we need citizens’ voices heard to move the White House from this position.

full_text:
In recent weeks, the new Postmaster General has terminated any overtime pay, which has caused delays. 

He’s also fired or reassigned career employees with institutional knowledge, exacerbating staffing shortages.

This goes so far beyond politics.

full_text:
In passing this amendment today, the House sent a bipartisan message that we need a full accounting of the threats Russia poses.

This is particularly important as the President continues to engage regularly with President Putin and seeks to move the relationship closer.

This is not new, but it’s critical context for the President’s cozying up to the Russians.

retweeted_text: Today, President Trump threatened to send federal law enforcement into many cities, including Detroit. Frankly, he doesn't know the first thing about Detroit. If he did, he’d know Detroiters gathered to peacefully protest the systemic racism that Black Americans face every day.

full_text:
We cannot allow our non-partisan security forces to become a politicized tool of any one president.

All Americans, of all political persuasions, should reject such a dangerous trend, done in our name.

full_text:
On 7/10 FPS told the Homeland Security Committee that visible agency ID is typically required for DHS officers & that they had checked to make sure officers were complying with this requirement when policing protests. 

But it appears that requirement wasn't followed in Portland.

The use of unidentifiable federal law enforcement –– lacking insignia and identification –– is disturbing to anyone with a respect for history.

full_text:
Just as important is the way federal forces were inserted into the protests:

First, state & local law enforcement did not request or authorize fed. assistance.

Every American should be concerned that any Admin. would insert fed. forces w/o permission of state & local officials.

His life of service to our country is a reminder of what the fight for justice looks like: courageous, relentless, implacable and open-hearted.

John Lewis put his life on the line in the fight for justice –– not just on the Edmund Pettus bridge, but many times in a righteous struggle to validate the high ideals of our nation’s founding.

His physical courage was matched by his moral courage as the conscience of Congress.

full_text:
Please wear a mask because it will help protect you, your loved ones, your neighbors, your community from a deadly disease.

If that doesn’t convince you, please wear a mask because it increases the chances that our kids will get to go back to school sooner rather than later. https://t.co/hOgwtHZlaW

full_text:
Our competitive advantage as a country is based on the idea that the best & brightest in the world want to make it in the U.S. Not China. Not Russia. Here.

Cutting our paying, enrolled foreign students is short-sighted, & puts politics above protecting our competitive advantage.

full_text:
Juneteenth is the oldest celebration of the end of slavery in the U.S. The day is an important celebration of freedom, and a reminder of the slow march toward equality.

Starting today, every year, our office will be closed on Juneteenth in observance of the holiday.

full_text: As the daughter of a woman who came out in the 1980s and lived the rest of her life knowing that discrimination could at any moment derail her ability to live and work as she wanted, I believe no American should have to live under that specter of discrimination.

full_text:
Today’s Supreme Court ruling upholds a simple and deeply American proposition:

In our country, your opportunity to contribute should not be limited by who you are, or how you identify.

As a country, we have not always lived up to that ideal, but today we take a step toward it.

During this crisis, there has been a near historic spike in domestic and gender based violence. Resources for survivors are crucial at this time.#thisiswhywework

If you or someone you love is experiencing violence, call the 24/7 hotline at 800-799-SAFE (7233) provided by @ndvh https://t.co/OlxAxaNgGH

full_text:
So glad to see Commissioner @SlaughterDE's resolution pass in a unanimous, bipartisan vote.

Understanding how systemic racism impacts communities’ health is an important part of the conversation, & this resolution is a step forward in making sure our policy reflects our values. https://t.co/30GHIOqYYj

Over the past 3 days, the President has threatened the use of “vicious dogs” and “ominous weapons,” and told Governors that he would deploy active duty troops to their states if they didn’t comply.

Sec. @EsperDoD described American cities as “battlespace” to “dominate” by force.

Our Founders worried that the Presidents would use standing armies to oppress the citizens, as the British had done, and turn us unto a garrison state.

They designed our laws to make it hard to use military force at home.

It is diverse and devoted.

full_text: As the wife of a 30-year Army officer, step-mom to Army officers, and someone who has worked alongside the military in a combat zone, what I have heard from the President on the use of the military in our cities –– with the support of the SECDEF and the CJCS –– has pained me.

full_text:
The bipartisan PPP Flexibility Act makes important fixes to the PPP program to make it more usable. 

I was a proud cosponsor and I urge my colleagues in the Senate to take this bill up ASAP, because it just makes good, common sense.

full_text:
I hear it every day: Michigan small business owners are grateful for PPP loans, but some of the requirements for our businesses are hard to meet –– particularly with so many of them not yet open.

Today in the House, we responded to that chorus of concerns.

I hope the Senate will quickly come to the table so we can find common ground, negotiate, and get small businesses the help they need.

full_text:
In the HEROES Act, we extended the time businesses have to use PPP funds from 8 to 24 weeks, and added flexibility so they can use the funds in the ways they need.

That’s good for entrepreneurs, for workers, and for downtowns across Michigan.

full_text:

Our businesses need more time.

I've spoken with city managers about the hard road ahead when local budgets feel the hit, impacting municipal services, public safety, local health departments, water/sanitation & more.

This is the time for bipartisanship. @RepSlotkin and @MayorBarnett provide a great example. https://t.co/3KgS04TNEv

full_text:
Supporting small cities and towns shouldn't be a partisan issue –– it’s about beating back this virus and getting back on our feet.

@MayorBarnett, President of @usmayors, and I advocate for more support to communities fighting COVID-19 in @DetNewsOpinion: https://t.co/DxjvsQjkqk

The @USPS has my support. https://t.co/z7bQ7WpuqW

Americans have the right to protest. Americans have the right to make unfounded claims about the virus and dispute the death toll of 3,600 Michiganders, as many speakers did today.

full_text:
I would not ordinarily advocate for legislation telling the executive branch how to manage a crisis, but I cannot ignore the outcry from my district and my state.

We need action now, and if the President won't use his authorities, I will do everything I can to push him to act.

I hope the president will take strong action to ensure vital medical supplies are Made in America.

full_text:
We have suffered because so much of our medical supply chain is offshore. We are fighting a war against #COVID19 but our armor is made overseas. 

We’d never outsource the production of jet fighters or combat boots, and the same should go for gloves, gowns, masks and test swabs.

full_text:
Mr. President, as you consider efforts to secure our supply chain, don’t make this a choice between punishing China or placating China.

We should care less about what China thinks and more about what helps keep the American people safe. https://t.co/WKZZqIV5n0

full_text:
If we don't allow smaller cities & towns to benefit from federal assistance, many could be forced to take drastic action––including laying off the very same personnel working on the front lines of this crisis.

I'm calling for future COVID-19 legislation to include this support: https://t.co/SkvDAIir5R

If you want an image of what a hero looks like, this is it.

She has to be sure not to eat, drink or use the restroom while on shift, for risk of spreading the virus.

This includes telling patients the final words from their families. https://t.co/qn2A89sSm1

FOOD DISTRIBUTION FOR THOSE IN NEED TODAY: 9am-1pm

Forgotten Harvest is at Civic Center Park (soccer fields parking lot) behind Township Hall and is distributing food to those in need today from 9am-1pm. No contact - food will be loaded directly into your trunk. https://t.co/MW6JJ3jlFR

This legislative initiative is designed to honor their efforts––& keep us all safe.

full_text:
Today I announced the Made in America Medical Supply Chain Initiative, 3 bills to harness America’s manufacturing might to our military’s unparalleled crisis logistics capability.

The guiding principle: ensure that we never send healthcare providers into battle unprotected.

full_text:
As a national security professional, I find it unacceptable that we were so unprepared for #COVID19.

As a Michigander, I find it unacceptable that we're losing lives b/c we lack equipment U.S. manufacturers can make.

It’s time to do something about it. https://t.co/mEKWHr9Qki

full_text:
This is David, a nurse from Mason, with his team. We spoke on the phone after I read the moving letter he wrote me on what it's like to work without enough PPE.

“We’re the soldiers on the front line being asked to wage war without even the bare minimum,” he wrote.

He’s right. https://t.co/QBwSkO7MoK

I'm so proud that @SenGaryPeters' and my Support for Veterans in Effective Apprenticeships Act has been signed into law.

.@Delta’s support will help Michigan hospitals and health care providers address the influx of COVID-19 patients and help us all bend the curve and slow the spread of this virus. Thank you! 

To get involved, please visit our volunteer website at https://t.co/WZ51AQdAZw. https://t.co/9xyYU0DVeT

full_text:
Our state still needs significant federal assistance on medical supplies & equipment. That’s our most urgent need.

And it will continue to be my priority to work with the governor and my colleagues in the congressional delegation to fight for MI’s front-line health providers.

retweeted_text: .@RepSlotkin: In Michigan, “we just simply don’t have enough tests or personal protective equipment. So that is our singular focus right now.” https://t.co/TMBhDheKnS

full_text:
I am heartbroken for the family of Lansing native Kious Kelly, who died while caring for others.

Our medical professionals are the front-line troops in this conflict –– we must provide them with the armor to protect themselves while they protect us. https://t.co/cZmjEMloOj

full_text:
Mr. President, we don’t need troops. We need tests. We don’t need the 82nd Airborne on our border—we need N95 masks in our hospitals.

The threat isn’t coming from our friends in Canada, it’s coming from the inability to get the supplies & equipment we need to care for the sick. https://t.co/ouYPTY80HO

full_text:
Would you send our military into war without body armor?

Our heathcare workers are on the frontlines of this battle, and we need to protect them so they can protect us. 

Michigan’s delegation issued a bipartisan call to @VP to mobilize additional supplies to our state: https://t.co/GIRdEDb1Cn

full_text:
I think of our frontline healthcare workers right now the way I thought of the first responders on 9/11.

And not providing them adequate personal protective equipment is like sending our troops into battle without everything that they need. https://t.co/3CPpulsZdj

full_text:
Our healthcare workers are on the front lines of this conflict.
We need to treat them the way we would our frontline active duty military in a different conflict –– and get them the supplies they need to fight #COVID19.
Our new bill requires the Admin. to act under the DPA: https://t.co/VLE5Nn0PS6

full_text:
The federal government's most urgent task is to accelerate the flow of vital supplies to our frontline workers.

Today @RepTimRyan, @RepJohnKatko and I are announcing the Medical Supply Chain Emergency Act, which requires the Admin. to implement the DPA to produce those supplies.

full_text:

As a member of the House Homeland Security Committee, I am engaging with FEMA on this vital task.

full_text:
Gov. Whitmer and other governors have asked the federal government to help to mitigate the bidding war between the states.

In my conversations with them, hospitals, health care workers and first responders in my district are increasingly urgent in asking for these supplies.

retweeted_text: Small businesses that have contracts w/ our federal government need expedited payments. I led a bipartisan effort w/ @RepSlotkin & @RepBalderson to provide that. Small businesses are the backbone of our economy, & we need to do whatever we can to lift them up right now. https://t.co/NI78eWHFLW

full_text: There is no doubt this decision will affect small business and workers, which is why I’m calling on House and Senate leadership to work in a bipartisan manner to advance economic recovery legislation that gets help to the working families and small businesses that need it most.

Michigan, wondering what Washington is doing about the spread and impact of #COVID19? I talked to @SenGaryPeters & @RepSlotkin about it and break it down here. ⤵️

What Is Congress Doing About The Coronavirus? http://https://t.co/EjPhYCwaZG

full_text:
Our National Guard are an essential force that provide highly effective response capabilities.

I sent a bipartisan letter with my MI colleagues to the President, requesting he grant @GovWhitmer's request for use of Michigan’s National Guard to aid in #COVID19 response & support: https://t.co/Bf0oXCFKCU

More than 1,000 health care providers a day cross the border to work at just one Michigan hospital.

full_text:
This resolution simply re-states what is already required by law: any President must get authorization from Congress before taking us into protracted war.

It states this while making clear that the Admin. always retains the right to act in self defense for ourselves or allies.

Today we took a final vote in the House to pass the bipartisan War Powers Resolution, which passed the Senate on February 13. This is the Senate version of the War Powers Resolution I sponsored, and that passed the House on January 9.

The next stop is the President’s desk.

The package includes:
• $2.2B for prevention, preparedness, & response efforts
• $3B for vaccine development
• $1B in loan subsidies to affected small businesses & farm co-ops
• $61M to, in part, mitigate potential supply chain interruptions
• Telemedicine access for seniors

full_text:
Bottom line: today's votes contribute to the conversation that started earlier this month around my WPR. 

Together, they reiterate what's in the Constitution: no President can take the U.S. into war without engaging the American public and coming to Congress for authorization.

full_text:
2. The 2002 AUMF authorized President Bush to use military force against the Saddam Hussein regime in Iraq. Given that Saddam fell in 2003, most believe this is an outdated, unnecessary authorization. 

The 2002 AUMF also does not authorize war against the state of Iran.

1. The 2001 AUMF, which authorized President Bush to use military force against Al Qaeda and its affiliates for their role in the 9/11 attacks.

This 2001 AUMF is very much in use today, as it allows for counter-terrorism operations against Al Qaeda affiliates such as ISIS.

full_text:
In 1973, Congress passed the War Powers Resolution (WPR) with bipartisan support. It says:

POTUS must notify Congress within 48 hrs of initiating the use of military force.

Military force must be terminated within 60 days unless POTUS receives Congressional authorization.

full_text:
PFAS is everywhere in our communities; nearly every living being has detectable levels of PFAS in their blood. 

We must reverse this trend. Clean water must be treated as a right, and we should view the threat to our waters for what it is –– a threat to our homeland security.

full_text:
The House passed #HR3 to allow the government to negotiate for lower prices.

My Real Time Benefits Act, which would lower out-of-pocket costs, passed w/ unanimous, bipartisan support.

The Senate must take the up or down vote we owe constituents demanding action to lower costs.

full_text:
This resolution is intended to have that debate, as our Founders intended, & to be clear with the public on whether their body has authorized war with Iran.

Members of Congress have a constitutional responsibility to uphold when it comes to authorizing the use of military force.

While we don't yet know the full extent of tonight's military activity, if it's indeed true that Iranians fired conventional ballistic missiles at U.S. targets, it would be unprecedented.

We are now in a cycle of escalation that threatens to draw us into wider war.

I was humbled to host a ceremony honoring Dick Thelen, one of 11 remaining USS Indianapolis survivors and the only one in Michigan.

The bravery Mr. Thelen showed nearly 75 years ago inspire me and reflect the values that we all should aspire to uphold. https://t.co/qgRn4F2bBc

retweeted_text: Everyone deserves access to quality, affordable health care. That’s why today, I joined @RepHaleyStevens and @RepSlotkin to encourage Michiganders to sign up for coverage during ACA open enrollment ending December 15th. To sign up for coverage, visit https://t.co/jU2yegoSEd today https://t.co/5OoE1EJEjK

full_text: I was proud to join @GovWhitmer at @CareFreeMedical  today to encourage folks to do so — and talk about our work in Lansing and Washington to protect people with pre-existing conditions and push back on the Administration's attempts to undermine the ACA. https://t.co/dQx6zjlrnG

full_text:
No one should ever go broke because they happen to get sick, and no family should have to decide whether they can afford to save the life of a loved one. 

That's why it's so important to sign up for health coverage through https://t.co/I7RRKTlXbq by December 15. #GetCovered

Over the last few days, I‘ve been in Turkey and Iraq as part of a bipartisan CODEL from the House Armed Services Committee. 

We have met with Turkish and Iraqi leaders to talk about countering ISIS, the U.S.–Turkey relationship, as well as our defense spending in the region: https://t.co/eoDLXs0Yml

full_text:
Saddened to hear of the passing of Bob Traxler, who represented our district in Congress.

He led with compassion, a love for Michigan and a commitment to bipartisanship –– and will always be remembered for how available & responsive he was to his constituents and our community. https://t.co/26EkGGYSyI

Seniors on Medicare should have their vision care covered. Period.

Eye exams & corrective lenses are an essential part of healthcare—but aren't currently covered by Medicare.

More Democrats are calling for information on the whistleblower complaint regarding President Trump.

"If these allegations are true, these are impeachable offenses," says @RepSlotkin, "So we are calling on Congress and the rest of our members here to do everything in our power." https://t.co/0nyyWMPxP9

full_text: I swore an oath to protect and defend the Constitution. If true, these new allegations against the President are a threat to our national security, and constitute an impeachable offense. https://t.co/4JrTEVl2Yn

Randy Freeman is the President of UAW Local 652 in Lansing. He has been a UAW member for 41 years.

full_text:
And it’s not just about this one story: when someone who helps provide information to our government fears for their life, it causes a chilling effect on potential sources around the world, who often take great risk to do so.

And where – as a member of a persecuted group – he had insufficient access to vital medical care.

full_text: The visit left me with an overwhelming sense of the extent of the tragedy of what’s happening at the border. It impacted every member on our trip. As we walked back to our transportation, to end the day, our group of 16 Members of Congress was silent.

full_text: What you can’t see is that, due to the limited facilities, 300 migrants have been ‘metered’ — or told to wait in Mexico for days to weeks — until CBP has space to process them. Given the wait, without money or connections, some families make the decision to cross illegally.

full_text: We talked to a women from Honduras who said she was fleeing violence. Another woman told us she took out a loan to pay someone $4K to bring her to Guatemala. If she is able to enter the U.S., she owes them another $6.5K. If she gets sent back, she still owes that amount.

full_text:
Humbled & grateful thinking of all those who served 75 years ago today.

My grandfather was among them, earning a Purple Heart & Silver Star for his service. 

The awards now sit in my office, a daily reminder of what it means to put country before all else. #DDay75thAnniversary https://t.co/DNIblSrksw

For 89 days, @senatemajldr has refused to take up #HR1.

Getting money out of politics and restoring decency and integrity to our system aren’t partisan issues.

We’ll continue speaking out until Sen. McConnell gives this bill the up-or-down vote it deserves. https://t.co/fjl6Dpv3F7

#PrideMonth means a lot to me. When my parents divorced in the 80s, my mom lived the rest of her life as a gay woman.

Though she passed away before she was legally able to marry her partner, I know she would be so proud of all the progress made, including the #EqualityAct. https://t.co/TuBdYIxO5q

Heartbroken to learn of the lives lost in Virginia Beach today in a shooting that has shaken yet another community.

Thinking of those who are grieving the loss of loved ones, those who are recovering from injury, & grateful to the first responders who acted swiftly on the scene.

That is our mission, that is our mandate, and to ignore it is dereliction of duty. #HR986 https://t.co/08zxKoMPZx

full_text:
My mom passed away in 2011 from ovarian cancer, and when she was diagnosed she did not have healthcare — she long struggled to afford care because of her pre-existing condition.

Today I shared her story for the first time on the House floor in support of #HR986: https://t.co/aIYb0rgVER

The #BeHEARD Act will:
✔️️ establish standards to strengthen harassment prevention in workplaces nationwide
✔️️ empower workers to come forward by providing new resources
✔️️ safeguard anti-discrimination laws so that ALL workers are protected under our civil rights laws https://t.co/C0E23SZD1M

full_text:
Our national conversation about sexual harassment is long overdue. 

Proud to stand with colleagues & survivors to introduce the #BeHEARD Act to update our laws – and change the climate & culture that has for too long tolerated harassment and abuse. #SAAM #TimesUp https://t.co/dZQ8KzLUMo

full_text:
Lost in the back & forth on the Mueller report summary is what it confirms: Russia sought to interfere in our elections, particularly through social media ads.

Stopping them from doing it again shouldn’t be partisan. My new bipartisan bill would make those ads illegal: https://t.co/u5iFnTA6bF

full_text:
We know that high levels of PFAS are found in and around our military bases — and we owe it to veterans & their families to make it as easy as possible to get healthcare to treat that exposure.

Proud to help introduce the VET PFAS Act today alongside my Michigan colleagues. https://t.co/dMlRUauECg

full_text: Equal pay shouldn't be a partisan issue — it's an economic issue. It's not only wrong that women earn less than men for the same work— it means that over time, women & families have thousands less to invest in their education, buy a house, grow their business. #EqualPayDay

retweeted_text: People are choosing between taking a pill or eating. Patients in our communities need access to affordable prescription drugs. We must put consumers first by fighting to lower the cost of life saving medications. https://t.co/4naKzTzbtf

full_text:
My mom passed away in 2011 of ovarian cancer after struggling to afford health insurance for years due to her pre-existing condition.

The Administration's efforts to strike down the entire ACA would take us back to that time––when people like my mom weren't able to access care. https://t.co/sdyXwjYjtq

John would have been so proud to see Democrats & Republicans come together to sign a landmark public lands bill to conserve and protect America’s wild plants, fish, animals, and their habitats. Smiles and tears all at once. 

-Official White House Photo by Shealah Craighead https://t.co/TtGviKMK86

retweeted_text: #ICYMI: This past weekend, @RepSlotkin celebrated the opening of her district office in Lansing, MI. With #Alzheimers advocates in attendance, she took the opportunity to present a donation to the @alzassociation of the salary she earned during the government shutdown! #ENDALZ https://t.co/oXWqXFS98H

full_text: Last night, our office launched the Brimley Congressional Fellowship in memory of Shawn Brimley, a dear friend of mine and of many in the national security community, who passed away a little over a year ago. Shawn was a veteran, and a brilliant and dedicated public servant. https://t.co/cKogaiAZFr

retweeted_text: How cool is your Congresswoman? Mine, @RepSlotkin, spoke on a panel celebrating the new women in Congress yesterday and then helped me get votes to be the @runningstart #ILookLikeAPolitician Ambassador! full_text: Congratulations to Lansing’s own @EwuramaAD for winning @runningstart's competition to serve as their #ILookLikeAPolitician Ambassador! #MI08 is lucky to have you representing the next generation of women in politics. It was great to be with you last week to celebrate your win! https://t.co/7yuPv9xjhS

retweeted_text:
Thanks to @RepCasten, @RepSlotkin, @RepGilCisneros, @RepMaxRose, and @chelliepingree for joining me to introduce the FLAT Prices Act in the House. 

@SenatorDurbin, a long-time leader on fair Rx drug costs, introduced the bill in the Senate. I'm proud to join him in this effort.

full_text: This important legislation would provide 60 days of partial paid leave for those who need time away from work to care for a new child or a sick loved one. No one should have to choose between putting food on the table and being there for the people who need them most.

full_text: To all the workers who joined us: thank you. Your personal stories make a difference. To all federal workers suffering during this time: you have my commitment that there is a group of passionate people in Washington working hard on both sides of the aisle to resolve this.
